<TEXT>
us rep donald lukens convicted of a 
sex offense that threatens his career is taking his case to the 
voters 
i apologize i made a dumb mistake im sorry the 
republican said wednesday in announcing for reelection less than a 
week before tuesdays primary 
the 59yearold divorced congressman was convicted of a 
misdemeanor charge last year of contributing to the unrulinesss of 
a minor for having sex with a 16yearold girl at his columbus 
apartment in 1988 
he was sentenced to 30 days in jail and fined 500 but is free 
on appeal 
robert bennett chairman of the ohio republican party said 
lukens displayed a lapse of morals and he repeated a call for 
the congressman to resign this is not a political matter its a 
moral matter he said 
on may 8 i am sure the voters will do the right thing and say 
goodbye to donald buz lukens bennett said 
ohio democratic party chairman james ruvolo said he wouldnt 
count lukens out he also said i assume hes given bob 
bennett heartburn 
lukens is facing three republican challengers former us rep 
thomas kindness state rep john boehner and bond underwriter mort 
meier three candidates are running in the democratic primary 
reaction to lukens reelection bid was mixed 
rita hardman of fletcher said she will vote for lukens i 
think he has a lot of undercover supporters that dont have the 
nerve to say im going to vote for him but will she said 
dan cook a republian said lukens legal situation disqualifies 
him in his mind i think hes embarrassing to the party i think 
hes embarrassing to the whole government he said hes not 
the good example that you would expect 
lukens had said since his conviction that he wouldnt decide on 
his political future until after the outcome of his appeal he 
filed for reelection but hadnt openly campaigned 
appearing with his mother he made his announcement wednesday 
before about 20 supporters outside the post office in this farming 
village of 515 
i apologize for the situation i allowed to be created 
lukens said i made a bad mistake but the mistake was not evil 
and not criminal im saying im not guilty of the charge 
boehner said he doesnt believe lukens will be a factor in the 
race and he called the congressmans announcement a lastditch 
effort to save his job 
i guess it surprises me that after all this time he would 
conveniently come to the conclusion that he ought to apologize six 
days before the election boehner said 
donald birgel chairman of the butler county republican party 
said lukens could win his supporters will be there at the 
polls birgel said theyre not going to stay home 
lukens served in congress from 1967 to 1970 when he made an 
unsuccessful attempt to gain the gop gubernatorial nomination 
after 15 years in the ohio senate he returned to congress in 1986 
