<TEXT>
police swarmed into a gritty park and clashed 
with squatters holding a may day festival tuesday night after 
people began throwing bottles to protest an abrupt end to a park 
concert police said 
the clash at tompkins square park in the east village left 12 
officers injured and several protesters were arrested police said 
dozens of homeless people live in the park tensions have flared 
the past two summers when police moved to oust the squatters 
concertgoers began throwing bottles when police turned out the 
lights to the bandshell at 9 pm because the band had a permit to 
play only until then said police capt charles hanley 
there were about 300 people there hanley said they got 
angry started throwing bottles it was basically a riot 
the injured officers suffered assorted head and hand injuries 
said hanley and lt dave fenton police apparently made their first 
charge after a parks department officer was hit in the face with a 
bottle 
rob nunzio 27 lead guitarist in the band antidote was on 
stage when the lights went out said when they shut the music 
off people started protesting the cops came in from avenue a it 
looked like hundreds of them people started screaming at the 
copsthe cops grabbed whoever was in their way and threw them 
down 
one cop got hit by a bottle while on stage and got very mad 
and started trashing our equipment said another musician jason 
goodrow 
later about 50 police officers wearing helmets and carrying 
shields and nightsticks remained in the park dozens of people were 
walking around the neighborhood knocking over garbage cans and 
setting trash on fire 
others sat down in the street by the park chanting at police 
officers the cops started the riot 
about half hour later at 11 pm a skirmish broke out when 
about four officers on scooters apparently tried to break through a 
line of 50 protesters the protesters retaliated by knocking the 
officers off their scooters prompting about two dozens officers to 
rush in pushing aside the protesters and dragging one of them off 
the squatter may day festival featuring live music 
contests and food began saturday and was scheduled to end tuesday 
at the east village park 
on aug 67 1988 the park was bloodied by a fourhour clash 
between demonstrators and police that left 52 people injured 
last summer there were numerous arrests during several 
standoffs between police and the parks denizens that began july 5 
when police tore down a tent city and evicted more than 130 people 
