bill with spending limits because it serves the partisan 
interests of the democratic party by curtailing republican 
fundraising advantages 
leading democrats responded with a willingness to consider the 
abolition of pacs whose donations in recent years have tended to 
benefit incumbent democrats over gop challengers but only in 
