we can either get serious or continue to make speeches and 
protect the status quo on capitol hill dole said were 
serious about this were willing to work out any differences with 
the other party 
but in the last week both party caucuses in the senate have 
moved away from the concept of flexible spending ceilings proposed 
as a compromise in march by a panel of experts appointed by 
mitchell and dole 
it would have placed fixed limits on how much a candidate can 
solicit from individuals and pacs outside his or her state but 
imposed no ceiling on small contributions from instate residents 
republicans in their package were willing to cut the current 
1000 limit an individual can give to a campaign to 500 for 
outofstate donors but rejected any limit on the totals that can 
be raised from either source 
democrats are still insisting on an overall ceiling that also 
would cap the amount of allowable instate contributions but they 
disagree among themselves on how much to curb pac activities 
