call for a ban on pacs as an unconstitutional abridgement of 
freedom of speech and association 
as a fallback position their package includes a provision 
abolishing corporate and union pacs but allowing socalled 
nonaffiliated issue pacs such as those maintained by groups 
on both sides of abortion gun control and environmental issues 
however the ceiling on contributions from those nonaffiliated 
pacs would be cut from a total of 10000 for both primary and 
general elections to 2000 
the gop package also would ban socalled soft money 
unreported expenditures by corporations unions trade associations 
and public interest groups 
the gop bill however would continue to allow contributions by 
individuals to state party organizations to go unreported 
