unification 
von weizsaecker the first west german head of state to visit 
poland began his trip just days before the two germanys and the 
four victorious world war ii allies the united states soviet 
union britain and france are to meet in bonn to discuss the 
international implications of german unification 
von weizsaecker was greeted at warsaws airport by president 
wojciech jaruzelski and prime minister tadeusz mazowiecki the head 
of the solidarityled government 
he is scheduled to hold talks with both polish leaders as well 
as other dignitaries including solidarity leader lech walesa and 
cardinal jozef glemp the roman catholic primate 
the west german president will also visit the former nazi death 
camp at treblinka and the city of gdansk where the first shots of 
world war ii were fired 
von weizsaeckers trip marks a new stage in the difficult and 
sometimes bloody relations between poland and germany 
west germany is polands largest western trading partner and 
its support is critical to the success of the economic and 
political reforms undertaken by the new noncommunist government 
but with an older generation that recalls the devastating world 
war ii invasion and nazi occupation poland harbors feelings of 
bitterness and distrust toward germany that has come to the fore in 
the rush toward unification 
poland is seeking a seat at unification talks to guarantee its 
postwar western border and wants a treaty with the two germanys 
and the new government of a united germany making the boundary 
permanent 
drawn along the oder and neisse rivers the postworld war ii 
boundary incorporates into poland 40000 square miles of land that 
was former german territory 
this week poland submitted a draft treaty to the two germanys 
and the four world war ii allies us secretary of state james a 
baker iii and foreign ministers from the other countries will meet 
in bonn on saturday to discuss german unification 
on the eve of his visit von weizsaecker offered assurances to 
poles on the border issue 
the essence of the border problem has been unequivocally 
settled we cannot argue over territories and borders in europe any 
more von weizsaecker told polish television tuesday 
todays issue of the prosolidarity newspaper gazeta wyborcza 
welcomed von weizsaeckers visit with the headline this german 
inspires confidence over a profile outlining the west german 
presidents long support for polands border concerns 
kohl made a historic emotional and at points controversial 
visit to poland in november the trip was interrupted for a day 
when kohl returned to germany for emergency meetings as the east 
germans began to dismantle the berlin wall 
</TEXT>
