<TEXT>
arpad goencz the writer and former 
political prisoner chosen interim president of hungary on 
wednesday dedicated his life to fighting the hardline communist 
leaders who were ousted last year 
in 1948 when the communists seized control goencz lost his job 
as a prominent editor and was forced to work as an unskilled 
laborer 
in 1956 he was at the forefront of hungarys shortlived revolt 
against stalinism and paid for his involvement with six years in 
jail he won a reprieve on his life sentence under a 1963 amnesty 
once free goencz began translating british and american novels 
into hungarian and later published several of his own novels and 
short stories 
by the 1970s he became associated with dissidents who signed 
petitions and published underground literature in a campaign to get 
the communist authorities to be more democratic and respect human 
rights 
he joined with them in founding the league of free democrats 
now hungarys secondlargest political party in may 1988 
a stout balding grandfather goencz was born in budapest in 
1922 he trained as a lawyer and graduated in 1944 from the citys 
respected university he immediately entered politics under the 
thendominant smallholders party 
the smallholders won control of parliament in 1946 goencz then 
editor of a budapest weekly seemed set for a prominent career with 
the conservative party that drew its strength from the farmers 
running hungarys agrarianbased economy 
the communist takeover in 1948 changed his fortunes while 
evidently failing to dent his commitment to democracy the twist of 
fate apparently made goencz philosophical about his newfound 
political stardom 
i would not call myself a professional politician goencz 
said when elected head of the writers union in december the 
homo politicus and the writer in me are one what is now taking 
place is the realization of my political dreams not of my career 
wishes he said of hungary 
after vaclav havel in czechoslovakia goencz is the second 
writerpresident in newly democratic eastern europe there is a 
great conspiracy of international writers goencz joked to 
western reporters after his election 
goencz was a surprise choice for interim president in a may day 
agreement hammered out by the free democrats and the victors of 
last months free elections the hungarian democratic forum 
the conservative forum expected to forge a centerright 
coalition government with two likeminded parties later this month 
apparently wanted to stress national unity as hungary faces a 
mounting economic crisis 
goencz is expected to be named to a full fouryear term as 
president once the coalition is formed and parliament in june 
passes constitutional amendments that would give the legislature 
not the nation the task of naming a full president as interim 
president goenczs powers are largely ceremonial and in line with 
those of the presidents of many west european states 
the president is commander in chief of the armed forces and is 
empowered to initiate a plebiscite negotiate international 
agreements and exercise clemency for prisoners under the current 
constitution the president may serve a maximum of two fouryear 
terms 
