legal and technical issues concerning tribunal cases us 
embassy spokesman leonardo williams said 
the 9yearold claims tribunal was set up as part of the 1980 
algiers accords that brought freedom to the us diplomats held 
hostage in the us embassy in tehran for 444 days 
secrecy is a hallmark of the proceedings which occur in a 
converted hotel on a quiet residential street 
the claims are handled by three socalled chambers each of 
which has an iranian an american and a thirdnation arbitrator who 
acts as chairman 
ninetyfive percent of the claims were filed by american 
companies against iran a small number were filed by iranian 
commercial entities against us companies and the us government 
