<TEXT>
a knifewielding mugger held up a messenger 
wednesday and escaped with 475 million in financial certificates 
police said 
the bank of england immediately issued a warning to banks and 
money market firms but said it would be extraordinarily 
difficult to use the certificates of deposit and treasury bills 
to raise money 
a bank of england spokesman said there was a remote chance 
the certificates and bills could be used illegally to secure a bank 
loan 
the messenger was attacked while walking from sheppards money 
brokers to another finance house in londons financial district 
the city of london 
sheppards money brokers refused to comment on the incident and 
police were interviewing the messenger who was not identified 
