distress signal at 320 am defense spokesman peter fry said a 
royal new zealand air force plane started a search of the area 
shortly after dawn 
more than 12 hours later the soviet fishing boat druzbha picked 
up three survivors who were clinging to floating wreckage amid 
25knot winds said a spokeswoman for the national rescue 
coordination center 
the soviet vessel also recovered two bodies spotted by the plane 
one survivor was badly burned but the extent of his injuries 
was not immediately known there was no immediate word on why the 
ship sank 
