<TEXT>
a conference on curing homosexuality 
through sports and therapy has drawn fire from some health 
professionals and gay activists who say homosexuality cannot cured 
because it is not a disease 
the utah chapter of the national association of social workers 
voted 65 last week not to allow social workers who attend the 
conference to receive academic continuing education credit for 
doing so the conference is set for friday and saturday 
evergreen foundation a group describing itself as a nonprofit 
organization of former homosexuals and friends is sponsoring the 
event 
evergreen president alan seegmiller a licensed clinical social 
worker said organizers believe homosexuality is caused by a 
gender inferiority complex originating in early childhood that 
can be turned around if a homosexual wants to change 
but psychiatrist r jan stout said the american psychiatric 
association dropped homosexuality as a mental disorder in 1973 
no one knows the causes of homosexuality but biological 
factors seem to be the most important whether youre homosexual or 
heterosexual stout said most professionals have a consensus 
view that psychological and social factors dont cause 
homosexuality 
we no longer talk about treatments or cures for 
homosexuality said stout homosexuals can change behavior 
sometimes through will power but that doesnt change their sexual 
orientation 
robert austin utah aids foundation said homosexuals will 
explain their concerns during registration sessions but they wont 
be disruptive you dont change peoples minds by stopping 
discussions he said 
seegmiller said his group has no scientific studies to back up 
the groups program because were more interested in helping 
people he said he knows of at least six individuals who changed 
their sexual preference from participating 
seegmiller said the group advocates therapy to deal with 
healing the inner child of the past the organization also 
sponsors activities traditionally associated with men such as 
basketball and softball 
the men learn skills that enable them to participate in 
athletic games they never learned before said seegmiller some 
have found it helpful to seek training in automobile mechanics 
whatever they feel is a deficient in their role that seems helpful 
to them 
