refused to endorse bakers proposals but he failed to put together 
a government opening the door for shamir 
officials of shamirs rightwing likud bloc say shamir will not 
formulate a specific policy until he has assembled a ruling 
coalition and his hard line could be modified if the centerleft 
labor party is included 
shamir has been grumbling for some time that us proposals 
focus only on his offer of palestinian elections and ignore other 
aspects of his fivepoint plan which the government approved may 
14 1989 
the plan called for an end to the state of war with arab states 
aid to resettle palestinians living in crowded refugee camps peace 
with jordan and a statement of principles opposing talks with 
the palestine liberation organization or creation of a palestinian 
state 
we have voted in the cabinet on the five points and i see 
these five points together with our assumptions as one unity 
he told reporters 
but the arab world is unlikely to accept broader negotiations 
except in the context of a unsponsored international conference 
shamir has rejected that idea because he feels the conference would 
be biased against israel 
