where the vein is located share a royalty of 125 percent of the of 
the selling price 
in march 1989 paul r cleary deputy commissioner of the wyoming 
state land and farm loan office wrote another state official 
assuming a value of 7 per ton and a royalty rate of 125 
percent development of the federal coal would generate over 180 
million in royalties of which the state would receive some 90 
