prices similar mined coal in wyoming sold in midapril for 460 
per ton on long term contracts usually 1525 years and 380 to 
460 for contracts under a year 
at 460 the federalstate royalty would be about 119 million 
at 380 it would total some 98 million 
guerin the interior department spokesman said the 27 cents 
is the value of undeveloped speculative coal with no mine nearby 
speculative means there is no current market for the coal 
the 27 cents is a raw product to make money off that 
product you have to put in all kinds of money to develop it he 
said 
to bolster the argument that the deal is unfavorable for 
taxpayers the committee released documents indicating the coal 
would be mined and not sit in the ground 
bruce a bugbee an attorney who will represent sloankettering 
