residents of this rural town are mourning 
for three volunteer firefighters who died while trying to help a 
neighbor clean out a 38foot well and were overcome by gas 
the deaths were the first in the nearly 25year history of the 
170member volunteer company in this mountainous region of 
southcentral pennsylvania said assistant chief robert covert 
they were goodhearted people covert said wednesday while 
he and others lingered at the firehouse thats why they got in 
trouble they were too goodhearted they would never tell anybody 
no 
james f chestnut jr 20 and richard l hershey 40 both of 
hustontown and thomas l lane 39 of mcconnellsburg died tuesday 
apparently from methane gas that had built up in the handdug well 
state police said 
about two dozen other people were treated at the fulton county 
medical center including at least six men who inhaled some of the 
gas police said 
the firefighters went to the home of nellie brown west of town 
