jaruzelski and prime minister tadeusz mazowiecki weizsaeckers 
agenda also includes meetings with solidarity leader lech walesa 
and roman catholic primate jozef glemp among others 
he also will visit the former nazi death camp at treblinka and 
gdansk the former free city of danzig where the german army 
shelled the small polish garrison to begin world war ii 
weizaecker told polish television we cannot assess the modern 
times without preserving memories 
i think that youth should have their share in the painful 
awareness that the germans were the ones who had brought war 
occupation and lawlessness to poland that they had done harm to 
many millions of poles even though they bear no personal 
responsibility for that 
with weizsaecker was foreign minister hansdietrich genscher 
who met with foreign minister krzysztof skubiszewski to discuss a 
treaty to be signed by a united germany establishing the permanence 
of polands postwar western border 
a representative of the east german foreign ministry will join 
talks on the treaty thursday the polish news agency pap reported 
we have difficult years and difficult months behind us 
the substance of the matter has been clarified weizsaecker said 
his trip comes as poland seeks security guarantees before the 
two germanys unify and it marks a new stage in the centuries of 
complex often bloody relations between the neighboring nations 
west germany is polands largest western trading partner and 
its support is critical to the success of economic and political 
reforms undertaken by the new noncommunist government 
but with an older generation that recalls the devastating world 
war ii invasion and occupation poland harbors feelings of 
bitterness and distrust toward germany in the rush toward 
unification embraced by powers worldwide poland has raised its 
concerns 
weizsaecker said against the backdrop of recent developments 
we can all agree on how much depends on germanpolish 
relations not only for our two nations but for the whole of europe 
we are all aware there are still problems of a psychological 
and material nature to overcome 
poland wants a seat at unification talks to guarantee its 
postwar western border and wants a treaty with the two germanys 
and the new government of a united germany making it permanent 
drawn along the oder and neisse rivers the boundary 
incorporates into poland 40000 square miles of land from the 
defeated germany the territory was to compensate poland for a 
larger section annexed by the soviet union 
leaders in both germanys offered promises concerning the border 
this week poland submitted a draft treaty to the two germanys and 
the four victorious world war ii allies the united states soviet 
union britian and france which will meet saturday in bonn to lay 
groundwork for unification talks 
the border as it is today will be inviolable 
weizsaecker said in warsaw 
the president said germany and poland share a mutual interest in 
ensuring reform and avoiding instability in the soviet union 
this german inspires confidence read a headline in 
wednesdays prosolidarity newspaper gazeta wyborcza over a 
profile outlining weizsaeckers long support for polands border 
concerns 
chancellor helmut kohl head of the west german government 
visited poland last november 
</TEXT>
