<TEXT>
news reports suggesting that one in four younger 
men in new york is aidsinfected are incorrect the centers for 
disease control said wednesday 
the publication medical tribune sparked a flurry of news stories 
with a report this week that in the new york citynew jersey 
region one in four men aged 2544 is seropositive for aids 
other news reports said the figure applied to males 2544 in new 
york city itself 
dr james curran director of the cdcs division of hiv and 
aids said the news reports were triggered when a cdc aids 
researcher told a medical conference in baltimore that a single 
hospital in the new yorknew jersey area had reported a 24 percent 
infection rate among men 2544 
that data is from one hospital curran said adding that the 
rate was different at another participating hospital in the new 
yorknew jersey area and a third has yet to complete its reporting 
its correct for the prevalence at that one hospital curran 
said but he added a single hospital cannot be extrapolated to a 
city particularly one of 8 million people 
the cdc in tracking aids trends across the nation is 
conducting a study of aids infection rates at more than 40 
hospitals nationwide to gauge infection rates among patients who 
come to the hospital with nonaids complaints 
editors at medical tribune said they are standing by their 
report which cited findings as presented by the cdc researcher 
dr tim dondero 
dondero was not available for comment wednesday he is currently 
in china curran said 
cdc officials said the study of infection rates at various 
hospitals is continuing and results are expected to be compiled and 
released later this year 
by their very nature hospitals are a good place to examine the 
results of blood testing curran said the cdc also is monitoring 
infection rates among groups including military personnel prison 
inmates and even american indians 
its meant to give us a broad look at hiv infection he 
said but there are wide variations of hiv infection 
the cdc has yet to release findings from the hospital survey 
and cdc officials would not identify the new yorknew jersey 
hospital with the high infection rate 
curran said even though the hospital survey findings should not 
be projected to the general population we dont want to say its 
not an important problem 
