president bush on wednesday honored the 1990 
disabled american of the year and plugged legislation to guaranteed 
civil rights for the handicapped because disabled citizens have 
waited long enough for equality 
bush presented the presidents trophy to david schwartzkopf of 
rochester minn a high technology professional who has cerebral 
palsy and is legally blind 
in remarks to the annual conference of the presidents committee 
on employment of people with disabilities bush called for speedy 
house action on the pending americans with disabilities act which 
has been hailed as the most significant piece of civil rights 
legislation since the 1964 civil rights act banned discrimination 
based on race color national origin sex and religion 
the bill guarantees access to transportation telephone systems 
and businesses professional services and employment it would for 
instance make it unlawful to deny a job or a service to someone on 
the basis of that persons disability or perceived disability 
no longer can we allow ignorance or prejudice to deny 
opportunities to millions of americans with disabilities bush 
said we welcome you the disabled into the mainstream of american 
life because it is your life as well as ours 
more than twothirds of the disabled americans of working age 
are unemployed bush said calling that statistic intolerable 
much of that unemployment stems from lack of opportunity he 
said 
every american should be able to join the work force to the 
fullest extent of their abilities he said i look forward to 
signing a bill that will address the needs of our disabled 
citizens and frankly it is my view that disabled citizens have 
waited long enough for equality 
the disabilities legislation protecting all kinds of 
handicapped including aids victims enjoys wide support in 
congress but republicans have sought to change the pending house 
version as business interests stew about sanctions that would 
imposed on employers found guilty of discrimination the senate 
passed its version last year 
the presidents committee on the disabled is a small government 
agency that focuses on developing employment opportunities 
schwartzkopf the disabled american of the year is program 
manager with ibm in rochester currently working for the state jobs 
department as assistant commission of rehabilitation services 
