<TEXT>
here are some main points of the agreement 
wednesday between the two german states on monetary union 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
date monetary union a major step toward unification will 
become effective july 2 until then and effective at once the 
official exchange rate for west germans and foreigners going to 
east germany will be two east german marks for one west german 
mark instead of the 31 rate in force previously 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
impact west germanys powerful currency will replace east 
germanys mark which is virtually worthless outside east germany 
this will give east germans opportunity to travel widely and buy 
western consumer goods but it is expected to cause wide 
unemployment as east german companies are forced to close as demand 
for their products drops 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
savings east germany pushed for a 11 rate of conversion for 
savings but not all savings will be converted at that rate east 
germans aged 14 and under will be able to convert up to 2000 marks 
at 11 those aged 15 to 59 will be able to convert 4000 marks at 
11 and people 60 and older up to 6000 marks all other savings 
will be converted at two east german marks for one west german mark 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
salaries salaries will be converted at a 11 rate 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
pensions east german pensions will be brought to the west 
german levels meaning most of them will be raised 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
rents also to be converted at 11 rate 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
debts to be converted at a 21 rate more favorable to 
troubled east german companies 
</TEXT>
