the food and drug administration on wednesday 
licensed the first test to screen blood for hepatitis c a somtimes 
fatal disease spread mostly through blood transfusions 
about 170000 americans contract the disease annually and about 
half the cases progress to chronic hepatitis the hepatitis c virus 
is responsible for about 90 percent of the hepatitis spread through 
blood transfusions 
ortho diagnostic systems a subsidiary of johnson amp johnson 
