a company spokesman 
the test is being shipped to blood centers across the country 
and they will use it to screen blood immediately kniffin said 
the test is already sold in australia belgium canada france 
germany italy japan spain and finland kniffin said 
the fda is recommending that all us blood banks use the test 
said fda spokeswoman faye peterson 
about 20 percent of the hepatitis c cases that progress to 
chronic hepatitis then progress to cirrhosis which can be fatal 
kniffin said this virus is also associated with liver cancer he 
said 
the federal centers for disease control reported 28500 cases of 
hepatitis a were diagnosed in 1988 this hepatitis virus which 
does not progress to chronic hepatitis or cirrhosis of the liver 
is spread primarily by contact with contaminated food and water 
hepatitis b with about 300000 new cases occurring each year 
is spread mostly through sexual contact most commonly among 
homosexuals and among intravenous drug users about 5 percent to 
10 percent of these cases progress to chronic hepatitis or 
cirrhosis 
</TEXT>
