hawaiians stood by stoically wednesday 
morning as the angry volcano goddess pele cut a fiery path toward 
the heart of this dying coastal town 
it may be foolish to deny the natural process that created 
kilauea volcano and now pumps tons of molten lava from it but its 
just as ridiculous to deny the ways of madame pele like the 
volcano she is respected for her awesome power 
the goddess large presence in hawaiian folklore shows how much 
respect the hawaiian people have for their land a product of 
ancient volcanic eruptions most kamaainas or local residents 
dont worship pele exclusively but pay homage to her for the 
beauty they live in 
its more a respect for the land and the volcano than a 
religion said reggie okamura of the national volcano 
observatory i have some belief its inherent to anyone born and 
raised here 
legend says if pele is not shown proper respect through the 
bestowing of gifts or if people try to ruin the land she has 
formed shell roar out of kilauea to vent her wrath 
ed lorenz has lived in the shadow of kilauea volcano most of his 
60 years and watched along with others as homes have been torched 
by the fiery lava two homes were destroyed wednesday and five 
tuesday bringing to 128 the number burned down since kilauea began 
erupting in january 1983 
more than 50 were destroyed in the past month in this community 
alone where 125 homes once stood only 31 homes remain others 
burned along the path from the volcano to kalapana 
several more homes were in danger of falling wednesday the 
volcano about six miles away has spewed lava to within less than 
270 yards of the heart of the town the kalapana store and drivein 
lorenz a believer in peles power says the goddess is as angry 
as hes ever seen 
if she wasnt mad she wouldnt damage any houses lorenz 
said ive seen a lot of flows but this is one of the worst 
lorenz says pele is upset with real estate developers 
geothermal energy drillers and marijuana growers for profiting off 
her land and not offering her sacrifices 
the east side of hawaii island is one of the few remaining 
places in the state where land is reasonably priced and many are 
looking to settle here 
geothermal companies are drilling in the wao kele o puna rain 
forest looking to convert heat from the volcano into energy many 
say pele will not stop her destructive ways until geothermal 
exploration stops 
theyre growing pakololo marijuana and making big money off 
her land lorenz said now shes taking it all away 
how many millions of dollars are they making and theyre not 
going to offer her nothing not even a feast and bring it to her 
what a bunch of dummies he said 
