<TEXT>
a neglected piece of land next to the 
crumbling berlin wall has become the focus of controversy over how 
to rebuild what once was the center of a vibrant capital 
it is the spot on potsdamer platz one of europes most elegant 
squares before world war ii that the giant daimlerbenz wants to 
erect a new headquarters 
fears have grown in both west and east berlin that the shopping 
spree for land is about to start and that large rich western 
companies will determine the citys future landscape 
what berlin does not need is quick projects thought up in an 
illusory and shortlived reunification euphoria east berlin 
architect bruno flierl said in an interview 
one of east berlins chief planners has expressed concern about 
possible economic colonialism by the west 
after much internal bickering the west berlin city council has 
agreed to take competitive bids in july for a contract to rebuild 
the former central district 
east berlin will play a role in the decisions only after the 
election may 6 of its first democratically chosen city council 
this has caused complaints that east berliners will have little 
time to study documents affecting their part of the city 
since the berlin wall was built in 1961 potsdamer platz on one 
western side of it and neighboring leipziger platz on the other 
have been desolate symbols of a divided country 
together they had been the hub of berlin and one of europes 
busiest districts that ended with the destruction of world war ii 
the citys division and the building of the wall 
since the wall began falling in november potsdamer platz has 
become a major pedestrian crossing point motor vehicles use a 
newly completed section of fourlane highway linking east berlin 
with streets in the west that were dead ends for a generation 
makeshift souvenir stands in potsdamer platz sell chunks of the 
wall and soviet military uniforms to tourists circus tents and 
vans have sprouted on nearby land that is empty most of the year 
construction of an apartment block on leipziger platz was halted 
last fall when demonstrations and protest ended 40 years of 
stalinist rule 
an east german border guard said the work stopped when hopes 
were aroused that the area might become the center of the city 
again not just another place to build housing complexes 
he said the west german chain store wertheim planned to put its 
head office on the foundation of the unbuilt apartment house 
asked how he felt about western companies taking choice sites 
he shrugged and said of the planners i just hope they leave us 
some green spaces 
other east germans feel more strongly 
it would be unfair if all the hightech went to west berlin 
while the east was used for cheap production and storage 
facilities said guenther stahn east berlins ranking planners 
that would be a colonialist concept 
west berlins social democratic party wants to attract 
investment to the city as quickly as possible and has welcomed the 
daimlerbenz plan to build a headquarters for 8000 employees 
we cant afford to keep such an investor waiting mayor 
walter momper of west berlin told his city council recently 
the alternative list coalition partner of the social democrats 
in the council does not agree and said in a statement daimler 
is not the star around which potsdamer platz plans revolve 
representatives of the alternative list the equivalent in west 
berlin of the environmentalist greens party say the daimler 
building would be too dominant in the square they also argue 
against a company that makes armaments occupying such a prime site 
if construction of the headquarters goes forward as intended in 
1992 the alternative list demands it house a permanent exhibition 
on the role of the concern during the nazi years and on the 
possibility of converting arms production to peaceful uses 
west berlin council members agreed in april on the basic outline 
of future plans for the city including priority treatment of 
public transport and provision of open green spaces 
they did not give daimler a firm commitment but said they and 
the new east berlin council elected in may would consider it 
