<TEXT>
no offense to mother nature and the folks who brought us those 
zenlike infiniti ads but the car can more than hold its own 
against rocks and trees 
the 1990 infiniti q45 is in fact a delightful car that 
impresses as subtly as nature does 
theres the understated yet warm and inviting interior of the 
q45 no burl walnut here but there is plenty of smooth leather 
soft roofing material and functional wellarrayed gauges 
theres the controlled but powerful 45liter 32valve v8 
teamed with fourspeed automatic overdrive transmission because of 
advanced electronics this engine doesnt spin the wheels but 
purposely propels the car with controlled ease the powerplant 
responds almost effortlessly and seems to never be taxed even at 
high speeds and in demanding manuevers 
theres the cars moonmobile exterior with door handles that 
mirror the shape of the auto and front hood lines reflecting the 
rounded profile of the vehicle its sleek 
nissan is justly proud of its flagship for while the cars 
early advertising showing rocks and trees but no vehicle may 
have missed its mark the q45 definitely has not 
positioned against the highpriced european sedans such as the 
39700 jaguar xj6 and toyotas 35000 new lexus ls400 the q45 
with a base price of 38000 is a solid competitor 
the money buys plenty of performance in every area including 
standard antilock fourwheel disc brakes that produce stable sure 
stopping its impressive to stomp on the brakes and find hardly 
any diving movement at the front end in the test car there was 
just a gradual dip in the front even when i stopped suddenly from 
high speed 
because the test car had the optional high capacity actively 
controlled steering the q45 also barely showed any body roll or 
yaw in sudden lane changes and side moves this option provides 
fourwheel steering that briefly turns the rear wheels in the 
opposite direction of the front wheels when needed and then 
switches them to the same direction at high speeds 
infiniti engineers worked wonders with the q45 suspension it 
seemed a bit more taut and less cushiony than that of the lexus 
yet i barely noticed bumps the infinitis 45liter 
278horsepower engine will push the car from 060 mph in 75 
seconds says nissan which limited top speed to 150 mph via 
electronic controls to ensure drivers dont vault into the next 
galaxie 
the 4liter lexus produces 250 horsepower and reaches 60 in 79 
seconds 
the downside is that the q45s fuel economy is lower than that 
of the lexus ls400 16 mpg in the city versus 18 mpg for the ls400 
making the infiniti subject to a 500 gas guzzler tax at purchase 
the q45 exterior is nearly as aerodynamic as the lexus 30 drag 
coefficient versus 29 for the lexus though the front end of the 
lexus seems a bit more square all metal seams on the infiniti test 
car were lined up with impeccable precision 
inside the q45 has wide soft front seats that are adjusted 
electronically and have two memory settings stitching in the 
leather seats lines up with back and leg muscles for maximum 
comfort the thick leatherwrapped steering wheel with air bag 
telescopes upward and tilts to the desired position electronically 
the standard bose sound system was terrific with big buttons 
for easy adjustment a sunroof cruise control heated outside 
mirrors and sun visors that had to be released from the ceiling by 
pressing a button were other features 
sitting in the back seat i tucked my toes under the front seats 
when they were all the way back on their tracks but my knees still 
didnt touch the seat backs and legroom was decent if the front 
seats were moved up a bit 
the middle passenger in back would have to contend with the 
large hump in the floor that accommodates the infinitis rear drive 
mechanisms 
the trunk was flat and deeply spacious 
bmw and mercedesbenz owners make up the largest group of early 
infiniti buyers infiniti reports that 50 percent of the tradeins 
have come from owners of those german makes another 25 percent of 
the tradeins are domestic models such as cadillac and lincoln and 
the rest are japanese cars such as maximas accords and cressidas 
more than 3350 q45s were sold in the first five months after 
the car was introduced in november infiniti says it does not have 
projections for expected sales 
the typical buyer is male median age 42 the company says a 
majority are married and most have household incomes approaching 
100000 a year at least 90 percent have college educations 
because the q45 is a new model consumer reports magazine does 
not list owner reports of trouble 
