<TEXT>
he may be 50 but that doesnt make bugs bunny 
an old gray hare 
the wascally wabbit and longtime torturer of elmer j fudd hits 
the halfcentury mark this year and the carrotchomping star with 
the brooklynese tongue is aging as gracefully as ever 
everybody knows who i am doc i dont cayuh where dey are or 
who dey are even in mars dey know about me heh heh heh bugs 
once said in an interview with the associated press 
success didnt come easily for bugs he had to change his name 
and work underground before making it big but hes enjoyed a 
career many hollywood stars living or sketched would envy 
he surfaced this year as a presenter on the academy awards in 
1958 he won his own oscar for best animated short feature 
knighty knight bugs the rabbit since has become a saturday 
morning cartoon fixture and makes more prime time appearances each 
year than bob hope 
on dec 21 1985 bugs received a star on hollywoods walk of 
fame admittedly not in the best spot he sits between cowboy 
actor rory calhoun and actress lurene tuttle who made such 
memorable movies as the clonus horror white mama and 
final chapter walking tall 
the brash bunny was the consumate of cool always undersized 
hes outwitted grouchy gremlins daffy duck and guntoting galoots 
in haredevil hare he defends the honor of earth against a 
martian with hightop sneakers named commander x2 
hes sung opera and tweaked the nose of pompous tenors he 
outraced tortoises and hounded hunting dogs 
and his rabbit hole was his castle to be defended to the death 
against developers and intruders of course you realize this 
means war bugs would say to those who provoked him 
youd never see bugs with a girlfriend and like milton berle 
hed flirt in drag to confuse a foe but bugs was his own rabbit 
fiercely independent and fresh 
bugs encounters with frequent foil fudd are regarded as 
classics the easilyfrustrated fudd was battered by bugs from 
infancy to old age in a series of shorts 
after tormenting fudd in one episode bugs turned to the 
audience and clucked i do dis kind of stuff to him all through 
the picture 
rarely did fudd ever turn the tables on his animated adversary 
once is a story in which elmer portrays a millionaire whos gone 
off the deep end he and his shrink keep repeating the same tagline 
throughout the cartoon my name is elmer j fudd millionaire i 
own a mansion and a yacht the oftrepeated line finally gets to 
bugs who checks into a mental hospital 
in another cartoon a wagner sendup fudd clad in viking 
horns sings to the strains of ride of the walkueres kill 
the wabbit kill the wabbit 
the bugsfudd battles most featuring elmer as a befuddled 
hunter have recently been honored in a museum of modern art 
exhibit and preserved at the museum of cartoon art the latter is 
planning an anniversary retrospective for bugs the 50th birthday 
will also be marked with widespread release of bugs video 
collections a primetime special and a special bugs magazine 
produced by life magazine 
its been more than his lucky rabbit feet that have kept bugs on 
top through the decades hes outlived the flintstones seen a 
future without the jetsons and continues to ride high in the age of 
the simpsons 
so what is it about bugs that makes him timeless 
bugs is a natural person leading a normal life until someone 
aggravates him then he fights back explains chuck jones now 
77 who directed more than 50 bugs shorts in other words hes a 
sort of counterrevolutionary 
bugs is hero to many of us he does the things wed like to do 
but dont have the noive to carry through 
his vintage cartoons are currently seen all over television by a 
third generation of kids in addition to saturdays he appears 
daily on national cable stations nickelodeon and tnt and is the 
toprated show on both 
jones admits bugs can be a bully or a nuisance so he took great 
care in setting the rabbit in situations in which he would remain a 
sympathetic figure 
mel blanc the man of 1000 voices who gave life to bugs would 
defend the rabbits honor if he didnt like a script telling the 
writer bugs wouldnt do that or bugs would never say that 
it was blanc who changed happy rabbit a niceguy bunny of 
the late 1930s into the rough and tumble rabbit weve come to know 
and love blanc ditched the wimpy name added the dese and 
dose of streetwise brooklyn and rechristened the character bugs 
the west as they say is histowy 
bugs debuted on july 27 1940 in the short a wild hare and 
he was off and running 
early on he became part of the world war ii propaganda pitch 
turning up a a draftee a superpatriot marine a real superman 
a rabbit the riveter assembly line worker today hes joined 
the just say no war on drugs appearing in an antidrug cartoon 
that aired last month 
through the years hes become even more underdog than he was in 
the beginning increasingly opting for brains over brawn such 
adaptability has served him well in dozens of shorts bugs has 
remained a hollywood trendsetter 
long before sigourney weaver battled aliens bugs went 
manoamano with commander x2 
forget field of dreams and other baseball flicks 
baseball bugs featured a slowballing bugs playing all nine 
positions and defeating the gas house gorillas bugs scales the 
empire state building for the gamesaving catch 
robert de niro as untouchable al capone the rabbit took on 
legendary tough guys edward g robinson and peter lorre in 
racketeer rabbit and bobby ds turn as jake lamotta in 
raging bull had little on bugs showdown with boxing brute the 
crusher 
theres much much more bugs as the straight hare in a jekyll 
and hyde sendup bugs evading two robinson crusoe types bent on 
turning him into roast rabbit torturing two french chefs with 
similar intent outwitting a rabbitbashing witch on halloween 
and theres more than a touch of bad boy in bugs in addition to 
his fudd abuse he frustrated yosemite sam to the point where 
yosemite screams great horney toads driven daffy duck near 
daft and dispatched dozens of animated assailants 
aint i a stinker he says in one cartoon 
but it hasnt been all good news for the rabbit over the last 50 
years the death last year at age 81 of blanc who had been the 
voice of practically all the warner bros looney tunesmerrie 
melodies characters was a blow to fans around the world 
but blanc didnt take the rabbits whats up doc with him 
his son noel and actor jeff bergman have taken over as the 
bunnys voicebox and bugs is still going strong 
to anyone who might think an aging bugs has seen his best days 
well as bugs might say he dont know me vewy well do he 
