<TEXT>
sometime this summer a burger king customer may 
leave an opening for a quickwitted clerk by simply ordering 
cheeseburger pepsi 
no pepsi coke the ordertaker will be able to say in a 
variation on the line that the late comedian john belushi made 
famous years ago 
burger king corp the nations secondlargest hamburger chain 
said tuesday it is switching to cocacola co as its official 
domestic soft drink supplier ending an association that started in 
1983 with pepsicola co 
miamibased burger king said cocacola products such as 
cocacola classic diet coke sprite and minute maid orange soda 
will replace pepsicolas soft drink lineup in its restaurants over 
the next three months 
analysts said the loss of the highprofile account is a blow to 
pepsicolas prestige but it would have minimal impact on earnings 
for either softdrink company 
pepsicola based in somers ny said the loss of the burger 
king account was not entirely unexpected in view of recent 
management changes at burger king it was acquired by the british 
conglomerate grand metropolitan plc in january 1989 and switched 
advertising agencies last year 
we selected cocacola because of its ability to provide a 
powerful mix of global brand strength stateoftheart 
technological capabilities and distinctive service burger king 
chief executive barry j gibbons said 
atlantabased cocacola controls an estimated 65 percent of the 
fountain portion of the us soft drink business and is the primary 
supplier for most of the major fastfood chains including leader 
mcdonalds corp 
recently wendys international inc said it was planning to 
switch to cocacola at its 1100 companyowned restaurants when its 
agreement with pepsicola expires at the end of the year 
pepsicola still has some major restaurant accounts including 
pizza hut taco bell and kentucky fried chicken all owned by its 
parent pepsico inc it also serves the dunkin donuts subway 
shakeys and ground round chains according to spokesman tod 
mackenzie 
mackenzie said pepsi hopes to continue serving franchiseeowned 
burger king restaurants but burger king spokeswoman cori zywotow 
said her companys franchise agreements require licensees to go 
along with its choice of a soft drink supplier 
there are about 5400 burger king restaurants in the united 
states including 800 owned by burger king and 4600 owned by 
franchisees 
neither burger king nor cocacola would estimate the value of 
the softdrink account 
burger king awarded its soft drink account to pepsicola in 1983 
after years with cocacola and reaffirmed its intention to stay 
with pepsi only last june 
but ms zywotow said both soft drink companies were asked for 
new proposals recently and the company decided to switch she said 
cocacola will work with burger king on new drink dispensing 
technology and marketing programs 
emanuel goldman who follows the soft drink business for 
painewebber in san francisco estimated pepsicola sales at burger 
king amounted to about 65 million cases or about 135 percent of 
pepsis annual fountain volume the switch would boost cocacolas 
fountain volume by 65 percent he said 
goldman said the switch should cut annual earnings of pepsico by 
no more than a penny a share while adding 15 cents a share at 
most for cocacola 
but in addition to lost sales volume the switch costs pepsi a 
valuable opportunity to have people to sample its products 
a lot of people go into burger king and see the name coke or 
pepsi how does that spill over into supermarket sales that is the 
part of it that isnt known goldman said 
jesse meyers editor of the trade publication beverage digest 
estimates the switch could add a percentage point to cocacolas 
405 percent share of the overall us soft drink market while 
cutting pepsicolas 307 percent share by the same amount the 
market is valued at 274 billion wholesale 
meyers said burger kings decision to switch may be a response 
to the recent rapid growth of pepsicos restaurant operations 
while pepsico is selling chicken tacos and pizza burger king 
is saying that competes with the share of stomach we are trying to 
fill he said 
pepsis mackenzie said there is more myth than reality to 
that line of reasoning 
