opec ministers began an emergency meeting today in 
an effort to curb overproduction to help oil prices recover from 
their recent sharp drop 
organization of petroleum exporting countries ministers began a 
plenary session at about 1 pm local time about half an hour 
later they broke up into smaller negotiating groups a tactic they 
sometimes find more productive 
all opec countries were represented at the session except iran 
whose oil minister was expected said kemal saiki opec information 
officer 
it is an ongoing circle of consultations saiki said 
the gathering was expected to last one or two days 
ministers made offered no comments as they began the session 
but they said when they arrived tuesday that they were aiming for a 
quick agreement on voluntary shortterm cuts during may and june 
how much output to trim and how the reduction should be 
allocated among the cartels 13 members have to be decided 
iraqs oil minister issam alchalabi on tuesday pegged current 
output at between 237 million barrels a day and 24 million barrels 
a day well above the ceiling of 221 million barrels a day 
saudi arabia kuwait and the united arab emirates are the main 
quota violators analysts say the uaes oil minister mana saeed 
otaiba said tuesday that his country was observing its quota 
the overproduction has caused a glut just when demand 
traditionally slackens in the second quarter and that has 
depressed prices 20 percent since january and well below opecs 
minimum reference price of 18 a barrel 
north sea brent blend the most widely traded international 
crude oil fetched a spot price of 1660 a barrel in london this 
