<TEXT>
eastman kodak co said wednesday its 
firstquarter earnings dipped 6 percent while sales fell slightly 
kodak chairman colby h chandler said he still expects to see 
positive results from the companys major restructuring last year 
in the second half of 1990 
barring unexpected developments in the economy we believe the 
recovery forecast for kodak will come about chandler said 
a strong showing by kodaks core imaging segment was offset by 
lower profits in its chemicals and information segments the 
company said 
while firstquarter results were slightly below those reported 
at this time last year they are consistent with the companys 
business plan for 1990 which calls for higher sales and earnings 
for the full year he said 
income for the quarter ending march 31 was 199 million or 61 
cents per share compared to 212 million or 65 cents per share 
in the first quarter of 1989 
sales for the first quarter dipped 2 percent to 41 billion 
from 42 billion in the same period last year chandler said sales 
would have been about level if an extra week of business activity 
had been excluded from the first quarter of 1989 
figures for 1989 were restated to reflect the companys change 
from a 13period to a 12month calendar year 
the rochesterbased photographic giant began a 549 million 
restructuring in 1989 selling or consolidating about 20 businesses 
and eliminating 7500 jobs 
chandler has said he expects to see the restructuring translate 
into better earnings and improved cash flows in the second half of 
1990 
david nelson an industry analyst with shearson lehman hutton 
inc in new york said the firstquarter drop was not unexpected 
the numbers are mixed but on balance positive nelson said 
the improvements from last years restructuring have not hit the 
income statement yet 
in the first quarter kodak margins held steady cash flow was 
positive and debt was reduced chandler said 
earnings improved by more than 50 percent in the companys core 
imaging segment because of lower operating costs and higher prices 
profits dropped 38 percent in the chemicals segment and 20 percent 
in the information segment 
chandler blamed the decline in chemicals earnings on high raw 
material costs and a power outage that shut down the companys 
kingsport tenn plant temporarily 
the information segment was affected by a soft us market for 
business equipment he said health segment earnings declined 3 
percent for the quarter 
