stock prices on the seoul stock 
exchange continued to rebound strongly thursday morning with the 
compostite index rising 3194 points or 44 percent to 75039 
points 
it was the years biggest singleday gain and followed tuesdays 
2979 points rise which brought the index up from an 18month low 
of 68882 on monday the market was closed wednesday a national 
holiday 
the twoday rally was prompted by the governments announcement 
of market boosting measures aimed at saving the market from 
imminent collapse 
in a midnight meeting of economic ministers monday ordered by 
president roh taewoo the government decided to force business 
conglomerates security and insurance firms to sell their land held 
for speculative purpose and use proceeds to buy stocks 
newspapers reported thursday that the government has ordered the 
top five business conglomerates to sell their land holdings within 
six months and invest proceeds in stocks it warned that otherwise 
they face punitive actions such as a cutoff in fresh bank loans and 
severe taxes 
it has been reported that many business companies have been 
engaged in rampant real estate speculation at the sacrifice of 
investment in production facilities in anticipation of high 
inflation 
they also have shunned investment in existing and new business 
projects concerned about waves of protracted labor strikes 
demanding steep wage hikes and more union rights 
the countrys economy has been sagging since early last year 
because of a slowdown in exports and rapid price increases 
